🧠 Context Engineering
The paper argues that Context Engineering is more important than Prompt Engineering.
Most AI failures are context failures.
Imagine hiring a senior engineer and giving them:
No documentation
No architecture diagrams
No coding standards
No project history
Performance would suffer immediately.
AI behaves the same way.
The Six Layers of Context
Instructions
Goals and responsibilities.
Knowledge
Documentation and domain expertise.
Memory
Previous interactions and decisions.
Examples
Reference implementations.
Tools
Available capabilities.
Guardrails
Rules and constraints.
Golden Question
> What would a senior engineer need to know before contributing effectively?
The answer becomes your AI context.
---
📦 Static vs Dynamic Context
Static Context
Always available.
Examples:
Security rules
Coding standards
Architecture principles
Benefits:
Consistency
Reliability
Drawbacks:
Higher cost
Potential noise
Dynamic Context
Loaded when required.
Examples:
Documentation
Search results
Database outputs
Tool responses
Benefits:
Efficiency
Relevance
Scalability
Best Practice
```text
Keep static context small.
Load dynamic context on demand.
```
This becomes increasingly important as systems scale.
